HEADWORD: Saunders-blue
<hw>Saun"ders-blue`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupted fr.
F. <ets>cendres bleues</ets> blue ashes.]</ety> <def>A kind of color
prepared from calcined lapis lazuli; ultramarine; also, a blue prepared
from carbonate of copper.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>sanders-blue</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

